<title>USA: AMCOL raises dividend, sets share buy back.</title>
<headline>AMCOL raises dividend, sets share buy back.</headline>
<dateline>ARLINGTON HEIGHTS, Ill. 1997-05-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>AMCOL International Corp, a specialty chemical and mineral products company, said Thursday it raised its quarterly dividend to $0.08 a share from $0.07.</p>
<p>The company also said its board of directors has authorized the repurchase of up to 500,000 shares of common stock after largely completing a similar repruchase plan.  </p>
<p>The dividend is payable June 6, to shareholders of record May 26.</p>
<p>AMCOL shares closed down 1/8 at 18 Thursday.</p>
<p>((Chicago newsdesk, 312-408-8787))</p>
